## 1. What the arc set out to build
(stated goal, from its handoff / brief / pre-registration — cite sources)

The arc set out to **bootstrap the V4 typed numerical-geometry kernel from nothing** — a substrate of typed results, explicit refusal, provenance, and no hidden rescue — to serve as the disciplined foundation for studying the residual-structure phenomenon Will describes in `where_i_got_stuck.md`. He states the intent directly: "I built the typed substrate and the primitives in the project files as my attempt at a foundation to do this properly — typed results, explicit refusal, provenance, no hidden rescue. That is the foundation." (`Build_Docs/where_i_got_stuck.md` lines 141-146, confidence high).

The Task 000 brief makes the buildout concrete: create a "Lloyd V4 bootstrap substrate" — a minimal `src/lloyd_v4` package, core status/validity/conditioning/provenance/result/protocol/calculus/serialization/error modules, the 12-axiom architecture documents, and guardrail tests (`Build_Docs/Reports/task000/task000_summary.md` lines 3-10, confidence high). The design-decision record fixes the substrate stance up front: strict runtime protocol validation, conservative status calculus that fails explicitly on empty/mixed/unhandled joins, compact-trace provenance propagation, **no V3 runtime dependency**, and **no legacy adapters** (`Build_Docs/Reports/task000/design_decisions.md`, confidence high).

The axioms authored alongside (`Build_Docs/Architecture/AXIOMS.md`, mtime May 11 22:06, same batch as the task reports) state the governing thesis: "Lloyd V4 treats numerical computation as navigation through stratified geometric spaces under finite-precision observation" — geometry precedes scalarization (Ax1), degeneracy is a stratum (Ax2), hidden guard rails are forbidden (Ax3). The intent was a substrate that refuses rather than silently rescues, so that the residual structure could later be measured without the instrument imprinting on it (confidence high; direct read).

Note on scope: there is no single pre-registration document for this arc. Intent is reconstructed from the Task 000 brief + design decisions, the per-task readiness statements ("Task NNN is ready to start once…"), the axioms doc, and the retrospective in `where_i_got_stuck.md`. The arc was executed task-by-task via Codex specs that Claude drafted (`Docs/session_handoff_v4_substrate.md` lines 224-259, confidence high) — a deliberately paced bottom-up build, not a one-shot plan.

